nt within its theological constellations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aChristianity and culture. 0aJudaism and culture. 0aSecularism. 0aTheologyxStudy and teaching. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Critical Theory. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849437140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438494371423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438494371/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles